Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.29,0:00:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a year, Saint Disciple Iska.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.66,0:00:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're that girl from prison?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.62,0:00:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Sisbell. I'm honored\Nthat you remembered me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.41,0:00:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I do apologize for breaking into your\Nroom in the middle of the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.45,0:00:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,However, um, I'm not accustomed\Nto being treated this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.99,0:00:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.83,0:00:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I would appreciate it if you could move...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.54,0:00:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, s-sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.26,0:01:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,0)\bord0.25\an8\pos(620,148)\c&H151618&}Our Last Crusade or the Rise of a New World
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.58,0:02:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How...?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.99,0:02:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady Sisbell must have been investigating\Nthat Imperial swordsman.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.08,0:02:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Could she have seen Iska and\NI meet in the neutral city?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.49,0:02:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,With her astral spirit, it's possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.54,0:02:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Please calm down, Lady Alice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.54,0:02:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady Sisbell's astral spirit can only\Nsee within the radius of 300m.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.49,0:02:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's impossible for her to see\Nan event in the neutral city.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.74,0:02:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe she heard our conversation\Nin the castle, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.66,0:03:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I was being careful, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.24,0:03:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps Lady Sisbell suspects you\Nand the Empire are connected?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.45,0:03:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,May I call you Iska?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.12,0:03:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm truly sorry for letting myself\Ninto your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.33,0:03:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I also didn't say a word of gratitude\Nwhen you freed me from that prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.99,0:03:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I must admit that, at the time,\NI feared it was the Empire's trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.87,0:03:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So please let me show you my appreciation now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.54,0:03:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I can't accept that.\NThat isn't why I saved you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.20,0:04:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,After you saved me, I read\Nabout you in the newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.83,0:04:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The Emperor's direct report had committed\Na crime of breaking out a witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.24,0:04:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That story had spread widely,\Neven to the neighboring neutral cities.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.74,0:04:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that why you know my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.49,0:04:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. And now, it is my turn to return the favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.45,0:04:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You lost your status and honor because of me,\Nso I will promise that and more.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.70,0:04:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I will guarantee your status and safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.04,0:04:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So please! Would you accompany me\Nto the Sovereignty?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.20,0:04:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.37,0:04:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a servant of the royal palace...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.16,0:04:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I do have a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.37,0:04:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.33,0:04:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.70,0:04:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're close to the royal family,\Nyou must have many people under you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.16,0:04:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not... I cannot trust anybody!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.20,0:05:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. I let my emotions\Nget the better of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.04,0:05:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I will come back.\NI'm glad I got to see you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.54,0:05:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.58,0:05:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.79,0:05:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We could not find anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.83,0:05:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.16,0:05:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I would like to offer a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.70,0:05:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.70,0:05:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If you would allow Lady Alice\Nto go on a long-distance trip...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.16,0:05:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady Sisbell is in a foreign nation, far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.95,0:05:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Since she cannot remain cooped up\Nin her room, she cannot hide anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.58,0:06:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If Lady Alice, her older sister,\Ntalks to her alone, she may confide in her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.29,0:06:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They are sisters, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.74,0:06:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Alice, could I ask that of you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.79,0:06:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.16,0:06:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Rin, go make the arrangements.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.87,0:06:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.08,0:06:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sisbell, what are you up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.66,0:06:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Sisbell?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.74,0:06:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This is unlike you. You simulated\Nall this a number of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.16,0:06:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I will try again. I will not give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.24,0:06:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We received new intel from our ally.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.91,0:06:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A purebred witch,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.79,0:07:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a daughter of Queen Nebulis at that,\Nis headed to the independent nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.24,0:07:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,By herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.49,0:07:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,She only took her servant. Without guards,\Nshe's as good as traveling alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.04,0:07:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What does our ally say?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.54,0:07:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That they'll give her over to the Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.83,0:07:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.08,0:07:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.62,0:07:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfect. Capturing a purebred is\Nour primary goal. We must not fail.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.54,0:07:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we deploy the {\i1}Object{\i0} ?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.79,0:07:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That witch-hunting weapon\Ncannot be tied back to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.29,0:07:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And nothing can stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.29,0:07:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us start the witch hunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.16,0:07:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, this is the life. What a treat\Nto have BBQ for breakfast.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.66,0:07:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When we were still in the Empire--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.08,0:07:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Stop talking and help, Boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.16,0:07:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll grill the meat!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.99,0:07:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, not yet, Captain! You have to start\Nwith veggies that take long to cook.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.49,0:07:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.58,0:08:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Aww, come on, don't spoil the fun!\NLet's go ahead and grill the meat!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.04,0:08:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Iska?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.20,0:08:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you can't. Right, Iska?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.16,0:08:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Something on his mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.37,0:08:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming, Elletear.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.49,0:08:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So could you elaborate on what\Nyou said the other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.12,0:08:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The ones trying to get in touch\Nwith the Empire...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.62,0:08:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,...are my sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.24,0:08:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You must excuse me.\NI wasn't expecting that at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.08,0:08:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming to me with such a thing\Nwill be disadvantageous for the Lou.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.04,0:09:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you want to tell me this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.04,0:09:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The future of the Sovereignty\Nis more important than the election.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.37,0:09:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand. I hear you loud and clear.\NHow can I be of assistance?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.70,0:09:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If my sisters plan to betray the Sovereignty,\Nit is my duty to stop them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.12,0:09:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I may not be able to do\Nthe right thing when the time comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.24,0:09:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,My feelings towards them might\Nget in the way. That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.91,0:09:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You want me to be the judge instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.45,0:09:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Lift your head up. It must've\Nbeen hard to carry all that weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.95,0:09:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll personally see to it to find out the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.37,0:09:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Please take good care of my younger sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.58,0:10:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave the rest to me, Elletear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.45,0:10:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This desert creature has evolved considerably\Nto survive the harsh environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.12,0:10:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,At the top of the pyramid is a large\Nbeast we all know: the basilisk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.99,0:10:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been years since I travelled without Rin.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.99,0:10:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}But please don't be alarmed.\NEven if we do encounter a basilisk,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.87,0:10:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a specialized hunter with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.58,0:10:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,W-We're terribly sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.66,0:10:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.45,0:10:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There are footprints ahead,\Nso please give us a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.08,0:10:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,E-Excuse me! You shouldn't leave--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.87,0:11:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not from a basilisk.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.66,0:11:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Smell of machine oil...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.95,0:11:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This doesn't look good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.95,0:11:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Iska. Are we at the hotel yet?\NI'm so tired, I can't take another step.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.70,0:11:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We're almost there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.95,0:11:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have minded staying\Nat yesterday's hotel again,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.45,0:11:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're so careful to want\Nto change our lodging, Iska.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.45,0:11:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm being economical with our budget.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.66,0:11:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We can stay somewhere with the same grade\Nbut cheaper if we leave downtown.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.20,0:11:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Something may happen again\Nif we stayed at that hotel...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.08,0:11:59.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to involve everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.91,0:12:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hold up, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.49,0:12:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's peeling off.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.95,0:12:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry! That's right, we need to\Ndo something about this astral crest, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.95,0:12:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't figure anything out,\NBoss, so just have fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.99,0:12:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That's so mean, Jhin!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.70,0:12:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Iska, Nene, and I brainstormed\Nand came up with nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.29,0:12:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better to step away from it\Nand go back to the drawing board later.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.33,0:12:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We still have 60 days.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.66,0:12:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.83,0:12:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you're worried, I guess\Nwe can go to the general market.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.83,0:12:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,General market?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.37,0:12:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an independent nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.45,0:12:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't the Empire or the Sovereignty,\Nso they have products from both.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.58,0:12:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Jhin, is the product we're\Nlooking for what I think it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.04,0:12:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the sticker Captain Shanorotte had.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.74,0:13:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We just need a similar product that has\Nbeen developed by the Sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.04,0:13:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Even learning the manufacturing process will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.70,0:13:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so reliable, Jhin!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.83,0:13:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we'll hit the general market\Ntomorrow morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.99,0:13:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.58,0:13:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go exchange currencies for tomorrow,\Nso you guys go on ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.58,0:13:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going out for dinner soon, so hurry back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.83,0:13:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.08,0:13:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Iska, give me your stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.16,0:13:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.20,0:13:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.49,0:14:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,She's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.83,0:14:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening, Iska.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.20,0:14:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of magic trick did you use?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.91,0:14:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I said I would come back.\NI will not be giving up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.29,0:14:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, but let's go somewhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.58,0:14:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just today when I\Ndecided to change hotels.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.41,0:14:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But you were already here before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.37,0:14:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this related to your astral spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.58,0:14:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It is as you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.33,0:14:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,My astral spirit has the ability\Nto display the past, like a video.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.54,0:14:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Today around noon, you called that hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.49,0:15:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You repeated the room number\Nand when you could check-in.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.16,0:15:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I was able to replay every past event.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.12,0:15:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow... A rare astral spirit that\Ninterferes with space-time, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.83,0:15:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But is it okay for you to give me,\Nan Imperial soldier, such crucial intel?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.83,0:15:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my way of showing my sincerity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.70,0:15:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, I lied about one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.49,0:15:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.58,0:15:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Sisbell Lou Nebulis IX.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.70,0:15:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm an official successor to the throne.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.79,0:15:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Nebulis?! She's Alice's sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.70,0:15:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't believe me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.99,0:15:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I believe you.\NThat's why I'm so surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.24,0:15:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But it makes even less sense. Why would\Nthe queen's daughter want me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.62,0:16:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone is after our queen's life.\NSomeone who's a descendant of the Founder.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.62,0:16:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But they're the same royal bloodline!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.16,0:16:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. This person is not after the Sovereignty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.29,0:16:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They're after something far more disastrous,\Na change for the worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.99,0:16:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If the queen dies, the next move would be\Na full-scale war against the Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.66,0:16:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Both nations will fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.04,0:16:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's their plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.87,0:16:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,To drag the Sovereignty into war,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.79,0:16:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and seize on the confusion\Nto eliminate the royal family.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.99,0:16:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They're after you, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.04,0:16:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I learned of this plan\Nwith my astral power.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.29,0:16:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I don't know who's behind this.\NThat's why I cannot trust anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.79,0:16:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Iska, I want you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.16,0:16:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you wish for death and destruction?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.79,0:17:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,A future in which both the Empire and\Nthe Sovereignty destroy each other?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.62,0:17:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you wish for such a doomsday?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.37,0:17:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.66,0:17:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why I ask of you to be my protector!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.12,0:17:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can defeat the evil going after the queen,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.95,0:17:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a full-scale war can be avoided,\Nthe doomsday stopped!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.08,0:17:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't ask you to betray the Empire in spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.95,0:17:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but I want you to change the future with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.70,0:17:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't good... It took so long to get here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.49,0:17:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The hotel Sisbell is staying at is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.70,0:17:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Lady Alice?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.95,0:17:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I was right! It is you, Lady Alice!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.79,0:17:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Schwartz!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.87,0:17:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What a coincidence. Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.41,0:17:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you seen Lady Sisbell?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.66,0:17:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.74,0:18:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't get a hold of Lady Sisbell.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.20,0:18:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,She went off on her own, saying\Nshe had something to do, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.20,0:18:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm with you. I absolutely don't want\Nan outright war between the two nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.04,0:18:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad you understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.99,0:18:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.33,0:18:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What? What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.91,0:18:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If the queen is killed, the Sovereignty\Nwill fall into the traitor's hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.16,0:18:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Then a full-scale war between\Nthe two nations will be unavoidable!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.08,0:18:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to avoid that--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.70,0:18:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the difference between us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.83,0:18:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.83,0:18:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just the full-scale war I want to stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.66,0:18:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to resolve the 100-year-conflict\Nbetween the two nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.70,0:18:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.91,0:18:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace negotiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.20,0:19:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That's impossible! To forgive the Empire\Nfor everything they've done?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.37,0:19:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Our people will never forgive the Empire!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.83,0:19:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that. But my reason\Nfor fighting is for that cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.20,0:19:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.91,0:19:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There's someone close by within\Nthe Sovereignty that you can rely on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.58,0:19:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's--?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.45,0:19:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,How disappointing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.79,0:19:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is such a heart-wrenching outcome, Sisbell.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.66,0:19:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Masked Lord?! Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.83,0:19:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a vacation to escape the hustle\Nand bustle. Nothing odd with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.83,0:19:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He's that guy who kicked\NCaptain into the vortex...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.08,0:19:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What is odd is you, Sisbell.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.12,0:19:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is the boy standing next to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.04,0:19:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,H-He's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.37,0:20:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No need to lie. I've had a run-in\Nwith that Imperial soldier before.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.24,0:20:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The queen will be devastated to learn\Nher daughter is connected to the Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.83,0:20:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't jump to conclusions, Masked Lord!\NI've not switched sides to the Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.24,0:20:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the opposite. I want to\Nsave our nation from a traitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.54,0:20:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the traitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.70,0:20:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what this is about.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.49,0:20:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The Zoas do not care about the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.79,0:20:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as they have evidence to gain\Nthe upper hand in the election.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.54,0:20:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You're free to think what you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.70,0:20:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too bad I have to capture you\Nfor suspicion of treason.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.95,0:21:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? You certainly are the queen's daughter\Nto still have the will to resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.24,0:21:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't go down quietly?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.91,0:21:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Chase her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.08,0:21:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Masked Lord, was it?\NAren't you on the same side?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.49,0:21:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,A traitor deserves no mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.12,0:21:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially since she's connected\Nto an Imperial soldier like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.95,0:21:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not interested in her reasoning?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.24,0:21:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter. Betrayl to be\Nwith the Empire is a crime in itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.41,0:21:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'm going to ask you to disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.49,0:21:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This is checkmate.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.12,0:22:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's...!
